“Imagine, Lydia,” said I, sitting on the table and dangling my legs, “imagine that all I’m telling you is fiction. Quite seriously, you know, I’ve been trying to make myself believe that it was purely an invention of mine or some story I had read somewhere; it was the only way not to go mad with horror. So, listen; the two characters are: 